sql:
SELECT SUM(count) AS total_rentals, SUM(available_bikes) AS total_available_bikes
FROM rental_station_data
WHERE station_id = 1;

SELECT MAX(available_bikes) AS max_bikes, datetime
FROM rental_station_data
WHERE station_id = 1;

SELECT available_bikes
FROM rental_station_data
WHERE datetime = '2011-01-01 00:00:00';

SELECT temperature_category_name
FROM temperature_categories
WHERE max_temperature > 15;

external_knowledge:
For the purpose of this query, holidays refer to special days or celebrations observed by the city or country where the rental stations are located; 
The date in the holidays table is assumed to be in the format 'YYYY-MM-DD', and the datetime in the rental_station_data table is assumed to be in the format 'YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM:SS';
This query aims to provide insights into bike rentals and availability at each station during holidays.

sql:
SELECT location, SUM(capacity) as total_capacity
FROM rental_stations
GROUP BY location;

SELECT data_quality_score 
FROM data_quality 
WHERE data_source_id = (SELECT data_source_id FROM data_sources WHERE data_source_name = 'weather_api');
